com.networknt.codegen

Interface Generator


  • public interface Generator
    This is the interface that every generator needs to implement. There are three methods that is used to generate project, get the name of the framework for the generator and get the config schema for the generator in order to find out how many options are supported by the generator.
    Author:
    Steve Hu

      • generate

        void generate(String targetPath,
              Object model,
              com.jsoniter.any.Any config)
       throws IOException
        Generate the project based on the input parameters.
        Parameters:
        targetPath - The output directory of the generated project
        model - The optional model data that trigger the generation, i.e. swagger specification, graphql IDL etc.
        config - A json object that controls how the generator behaves.
        Throws:
        IOException - throws IOException

      • getFramework

        String getFramework()
        Get generator name
        Returns:
        The generator name and it is used in the -f option in the command line.

      • getConfigSchema

        default ByteBuffer getConfigSchema()

        Get the config schema for the generator.
        Returns:

        Throws:

      • transfer

        default void transfer(String folder,
                      String path,
                      String filename,
                      com.fizzed.rocker.runtime.DefaultRockerModel rockerModel)
               throws IOException
        This is a default method used by all generators to transfer a template into a generated file into the right location.
        Parameters:
        folder - The output folder of the project
        path - Current file path in the output folder
        filename - Current filename in the output folder
        rockerModel - The rocker template class compiled from the template for this file.
        Throws:
        IOException - throws IOException
